Back on the Men’s World Championship beat and it’s great to be back! 

This tourney is underrated.  Here’s a look at some fun through the first few days! 

Pic 1: me and Kev by Riga sign, not that exciting

Pic 2: Dario Simions childhood friends by far were having the most fun, dressed up as beer bottles.  They enjoyed a couple themselves too. 🍻

Pic 3: Jake Middleton making some kids Moms boyfriends day. (Got all that? Read the sign) 😂

Pic 4 : it’s actually a video of me interviewing Jakob Zboril while Czechia fans were cheering their butts off (for the entire interview). No I couldn’t hear a word he said. But man, what an awesome experience. 

Pic 5 : Spiky, the mascot

Pic 6 : Simions pals, having no fun of course

Cabot you NEVER disappoint! 
THANK YOU for making Eddies 40th a birthday I’ll never be able to top. 

Kerry & Mike THANK YOU for being the best travel pals. We love you both dearly.  You made the trip that much better. 

James!  Thanks for crashing Ed’s party.  You’re pals are a blast, I’m glad we dragged you out every night.  Now ice that elbow. 

Our Captain Conrad, you’re a living legend. THANK YOU for an unforgettable dinner. 

My guy Lewis, best Caddie ever.  Sudbury connection was strong, pal. Thanks for a fun day. 

Ted, Edwin, Mearle, Andrew and everyone at Cabot thank you for treating us like family. 

This place is heaven to me.  I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again, East coast is the best coast. It just hits different. 

Happy 40th babe ♥️

(MASSIVE shout out and THANK YOU to Nana (@deberoo55 ) and @britt.bonhomme for watching our kids so we could make the trip!!)

Dear Sudbury, 

Thank you for an amazing 4 days of hockey.  Thanks for your commitment to having fun while working your butt off to get better. Thank you for loving the game as much as I do.  Thanks for helping me fall back in love with teaching it. Thank you for everything you’ve given me.  I hope I gave a bit back during that week in August…I promise to keep giving back until I can’t anymore. 

@nhasudbury Thank you for caring about the game more than the bottom line.  Your commitment to northern hockey is unmatched.  Couldn’t have done this without you.  Can’t wait for next year. 

To the ladies that took the time out of their busy schedule to come teach, I appreciate you more than you know. Thanks for being the best role models and friends. 

Coach Muzerall (@ohiostatewhky ) @matt_nichol & @sylvietetrault thank you for sharing your expertise 🙏 you are game changers. 

To @ccmhockey thanks for treating some lucky campers to new skates and sticks.  Your generosity didn’t go unnoticed. 

- Tess

September 18, 2023 was a long time coming…but man was it worth the wait. 
.
It was a special feeling in Barbara Frum Atrium today.  Everyone came together.  All the television networks shared their talent, simultaneously aired the draft so all Canadians could watch, and knew that today was a MASSIVE day in women’s hockey (and sport) history and did it up to the nines. 
.
I felt a lot of love in that room, I wanted to hug everyone. I couldn’t stop smiling and haven’t stopped since I woke up this morning.
.
What a great freaking day.  I’m crying writing this (while smiling). This is just the best.  I don’t have the words, I just have all the feelings right now.
.
Shout out to everyone who made it happen, @jaynahefford I’m looking at you ♥️ The players who stayed committed, THANK YOU
.
Can’t forget my girl @alicia.nikole thanks for stepping up and doing my makeup along with many others at the draft. Thank you for making every side my good side, because we all know I didn’t wake up looking like that 😘
Shout out to Balance blades for helping feed into Theo’s confidence on the ice!  Now the transition to hockey skates begins!

One of my favourite parts of filming Shoresy are the road trips back to Toronto with @jayonrait because I get to treat him to my favourite Sudbury eateries. 

This time around @donspizzasudbury hooked up a solid pie for our cruise back to the big smoke…And boy did it hit the spot!! 

Shout out to Max for making it happen. You legend, you 🙏♥️

Hi Canada! Kruger is launching its 4th season of the Big Assist Program 🏒. Let’s make hockey more accessible for everyone and get more kids on the ice! Nominate your minor hockey association to win up to $100,000 ⭐ #KrugerBigAssist

Earlier this month, I had the privilege of attending the @KrugerBigAssist Hockey Day event where we celebrated the return of the #KrugerBigAssist program. This is a fantastic initiative that helps make hockey more accessible and inclusive for families, so all kids can play Canada’s game.
I loved meeting so many youth players and sharing the importance of assists, both on and off the ice. Thanks to everyone for coming out!

Through the Kruger Big Assist, Canadians can nominate a minor hockey association for their chance to receive $100,000! Nominate a minor hockey association at KrugerBigAssist.ca!
